POPOVER.READING_THIS_MOMENT: It is the field representing how many hours the data in the table to be read will be read until now. E.G: Normalize the Data in the Last 24 Hours
POPOVER.TASK.ALL_ATTRIBUTES_INCLUDED: It Is To Check The Values Of All Attributes In The Raw Data Table.
POPOVER.TASK.DATA_TYPE: While Writing Data to the Normalized Table, Start (10:00), End (12:00) or Start-Finish Mid (11:00) Times in the Date Field, "Time Part Interval" Information Example (10:00-12:00 as an Example) It is the field that indicates which of the dates will be written.
POPOVER.TASK.NORMALIZATION: This Task Type Performs Min-Max Normalization According to a Timeseries Attribute in the Source Table You Have Selected.
POPOVER.TASK.RAW_DATA: This Task Type Provides Checking Whether the Values of the Data in the Raw Data Table Are Conforming to the Value Range Given to the Data's attribute.
POPOVER.TASK.RAW_DATA_CONTROL: Represents the Id of the attribute whose value will be checked in the raw data table
POPOVER.TASK.READ_DATA_FROM: This field that specifies the date the data will be read.
POPOVER.TASK.READ_DATA_TO: This field that specifies the date until the data will be read.
POPOVER.TASK.SOURCE_ATTRIBUTE_ID: It is the field that represents the data of which property will be read in the table to be read.
POPOVER.TASK.TARGET_ATTRIBUTE_ID: It is the field that represents the property of the newly created data in the table to be written.
POPOVER.TASK.TIME_PART_INTERVAL: It Represents The Amount Of Division Of The Data To Be Read Into Certain Time Periods. E.G: If the Read Data Happened Between 10:00 and 16:00 on the Same Day and "Time Part Interval" is equal to 2 Hours, 10:00-12:00, 12:00-14:00 and 14:00-16:00 Time Values in the ranges are summed and normalized.
POPOVER.TASK_GROUP.AIRFLOW_DELAY: This field represents the minutes between retry attempts when a DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) Run in Airflow Fails. NOTE: Enter 0 if you don't want DAG Run to be retried or if you want the retry attempts to happen right after each other.
POPOVER.TASK_GROUP.AIRFLOW_START_DATE: It Represents The Starting Date Of DAGs (Directed Acyclic Graph) to Work in Airflow.
POPOVER.TASK_GROUP.AIRFLOW_TIMING_INTERV: This field represents How Long DAGs (Directed Acyclic Graph) will work in Airflow according to the selected time type. E.G: When 'Timing Interval Type' is Day and 'Schedule Interval Duration' is 2 the Result is 'Run DAG Every 2 Days'.
This field represents What Kind of Time DAGs (Directed Acyclic Graph) will work in Airflow. E.G: 'Run DAG By Minutes, Hours or Days'.
POPOVER.TASK_GROUP.AIRFLOW_TRY: This field, if desired, represents the number of times a DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) run to be retried when it fails. NOTE: Enter 0 if you do not want it to be retried.
POPOVER.TIME_SERIES_ATTRIBUTE.COLOR: This field used for markers in the Geomap Dashboard in Grafana. According to the values you give to the attributes, a threshold is set between the lowest and the highest, and colors are given from green to red. E.G: If there are 3 attributes in total; Attribute-1 => Color: 10 (Green) Attribute-2 => Color: 40 (Yellow) Attribute-3 => Color: 70 (Red)
POPOVER.TIME_SERIES_ATTRIBUTE.LINK: You need to use keywords {crewIdentityNumber} for Crew Unique Id and {attributeIdentityNumber} for Time Series Attribute Id. (Curly Braces Included.)
